  "text": "In obese children and adolescents, insulin resistance is the best predictor for the development of IGT (39) and T2DM [CITATION_1] . T2DM is a progressive disease with a gradual increase in insulin resistance associated later with a decline in insulin secretion with fasting hyperglycemia. Over the last decade, there has been an alarming increase of T2DM in youth, concomitant with the rise of obesity in this age group [CITATION_2] and in the USA T2DM now accounts between 8 and 45% of all cases of diabetes diagnosed among children and adolescents [CITATION_3] .",
